<!-- ABOUT / HYPERTENSION -->
<section id="about">
  <h2>Hypertension Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Hypertension (high blood pressure) is a chronic medical condition where the force of blood against artery walls is consistently too high. 
    It is a major risk factor for heart disease, stroke, and kidney failure. Proper medication adherence is essential in controlling blood pressure and preventing complications.
  </p>
</section>

<!-- IMPORTANCE -->
<section id="importance">
  <h2>Why Medication Adherence Matters in Hypertension</h2>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Prevents Complications</h3>
    <p>Reduces risk of stroke, heart attack, and kidney damage.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Controls Blood Pressure</h3>
    <p>Ensures blood pressure remains within a safe range.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Improves Quality of Life</h3>
    <p>Patients experience fewer symptoms and hospital visits.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TIPS -->
<section id="tips">
  <h2>How to Improve Adherence</h2>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Take Medication Daily</h3>
    <p>Follow prescriptions exactly as directed by healthcare providers.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Monitor Blood Pressure</h3>
    <p>Regular monitoring helps track progress and effectiveness.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Healthy Lifestyle</h3>
    <p>Reduce salt intake, exercise regularly, and avoid smoking.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Use Reminders</h3>
    <p>Set alarms or use pill organizers to avoid missed doses.</p>
  </div>
</section>

